"{\"value\":{\"mdx\":\"# Getting Started\\n\\n## Installation\\n\\nThe ZCAM SDK is divided into standalone packages. For the quickstart example which performs a full flow of capturing, proving and verifying a photo, we will install the respective libraries. Note the packages rely on native code along with Rust bindings which need to be installed after package installation.\\n\\n```bash\\nnpm i react-native-zcam1-capture react-native-zcam1-prove react-native-zcam1-verify\\ncd ios && pod install\\n```\\n\\n*TODO: Need to add comments about setting up bundle id etc. How can we minimize the work required here?*\\n\\n## Quickstart\\n\\n*Todo*\\n\",\"document\":[{\"href\":\"/getting-started#getting-started\",\"html\":\"</header>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/getting-started.mdx#getting-started\",\"isPage\":true,\"text\":\"\\n\",\"title\":\"Getting Started\",\"titles\":[]},{\"href\":\"/getting-started#installation\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>The ZCAM SDK is divided into standalone packages. For the quickstart example which performs a full flow of capturing, proving and verifying a photo, we will install the respective libraries. Note the packages rely on native code along with Rust bindings which need to be installed after package installation.</p>\\n<pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\\\">npm</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> i</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> react-native-zcam1-capture</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> react-native-zcam1-prove</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> react-native-zcam1-verify</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\">cd</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> ios</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> &amp;&amp; </span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\\\">pod</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> install</span></span></code></pre>\\n<p><em>TODO: Need to add comments about setting up bundle id etc. How can we minimize the work required here?</em></p>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/getting-started.mdx#installation\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nThe ZCAM SDK is divided into standalone packages. For the quickstart example which performs a full flow of capturing, proving and verifying a photo, we will install the respective libraries. Note the packages rely on native code along with Rust bindings which need to be installed after package installation.\\nnpm i react-native-zcam1-capture react-native-zcam1-prove react-native-zcam1-verify\\ncd ios &amp;&amp; pod install\\nTODO: Need to add comments about setting up bundle id etc. How can we minimize the work required here?\\n\",\"title\":\"Installation\",\"titles\":[\"Getting Started\"]},{\"href\":\"/getting-started#quickstart\",\"html\":\"\\n<p><em>Todo</em></p>\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/getting-started.mdx#quickstart\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nTodo\",\"title\":\"Quickstart\",\"titles\":[\"Getting Started\"]}]}}"
